---

<MainLayout
  title="Real-World AI | Ron Keesing"
  description="Selected examples of AI deployed in operational environments where trust, reliability, and measurable outcomes matter."
>
  <Header activePage="real-world-ai" />

  <main>
    <section class="page-introduction">
      <div class="site-container">
        <h1>Real-World AI</h1>

        <p>
          Throughout my career I've had the opportunity to work on—and later
          oversee—the development and deployment of AI systems across a wide
          range of mission-critical applications. From autonomous spacecraft
          and maritime systems to healthcare, transportation, critical
          infrastructure, and decision intelligence, these efforts span nearly
          three decades of applying AI to complex real-world challenges.
        </p>

        <p class="scope-note">
          The examples below are representative rather than comprehensive. They
          illustrate publicly disclosed programs and technologies that reflect
          both the evolution of AI and my own journey helping bring it into
          operational use.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Autonomy -->
    <section
      class="capability-section site-container"
      id="autonomy"
      aria-labelledby="autonomy-heading"
    >
      <div class="capability-header">
        <img
          src="/images/autonomy.png"
          alt=""
          class="capability-thumbnail"
          aria-hidden="true"
        />

        <div class="capability-header-content">
          <SectionHeader
            title="Autonomy"
            id="autonomy-heading"
          />

          <p class="capability-introduction">
            Autonomy extends human capability by enabling systems to perceive,
            plan, decide, and act with progressively less direct human control. But deploying these systems into the real world requires dealing with edge cases, managing uncertainty, and developing comprehensive assurance regimes.
            I've had the opportunity to work on, oversee, and help deploy rigorously tested autonomous
            systems spanning space, maritime, and airborne domains.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="example-list">
        {
          autonomyExamples.map((item) => (
            <article class="example">
              <div class="example-description">
                <h3>{item.capability}</h3>
                <p>{item.examples}</p>
              </div>

              <div class="example-reference">
                <p class="reference-type">{item.referenceType}</p>

                <a
                  href={item.referenceUrl}
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"
                  aria-label={`${item.referenceTitle}, opens in a new tab`}
                >
                  <span class="reference-title">
                    {item.referenceTitle}
                  </span>

                  <span class="reference-source">
                    {item.referenceSource}
                  </span>

                  <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">↗</span>
                </a>
              </div>
            </article>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Security -->
    <section
      class="capability-section site-container"
      id="security"
      aria-labelledby="security-heading"
    >
      <div class="capability-header">
        <img
          src="/images/security.png"
          alt=""
          class="capability-thumbnail"
          aria-hidden="true"
        />

        <div class="capability-header-content">
          <SectionHeader
            title="Security"
            id="security-heading"
          />

          <p class="capability-introduction">
            AI in security applications helps protect people, infrastructure, and organizations by
            helping detect threats and support timely decisions. I've been a part
            of designing, building, delivering, and governing AI systems spanning
            cybersecurity, aviation security, cargo inspection, and physical
            security.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="example-list">
        {
          securityExamples.map((item) => (
            <article class="example">
              <div class="example-description">
                <h3>{item.capability}</h3>
                <p>{item.examples}</p>
              </div>

              <div class="example-reference">
                <p class="reference-type">{item.referenceType}</p>

                <a
                  href={item.referenceUrl}
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"
                  aria-label={`${item.referenceTitle}, opens in a new tab`}
                >
                  <span class="reference-title">
                    {item.referenceTitle}
                  </span>

                  <span class="reference-source">
                    {item.referenceSource}
                  </span>

                  <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">↗</span>
                </a>
              </div>
            </article>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Transportation -->
    <section
      class="capability-section site-container"
      id="transportation"
      aria-labelledby="transportation-heading"
    >
      <div class="capability-header">
        <img
          src="/images/transportation.png"
          alt=""
          class="capability-thumbnail"
          aria-hidden="true"
        />

        <div class="capability-header-content">
          <SectionHeader
            title="Transportation"
            id="transportation-heading"
          />

          <p class="capability-introduction">
            Applied to transportation, AI can improve the safety, efficiency, and resilience
            of systems that move people and goods. Examples of AI solutions I've
            worked on and governed include mission-critical
            software, aviation operations, and logistics and supply chains.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="example-list">
        {
          transportationExamples.map((item) => (
            <article class="example">
              <div class="example-description">
                <h3>{item.capability}</h3>
                <p>{item.examples}</p>
              </div>

              <div class="example-reference">
                <p class="reference-type">{item.referenceType}</p>

                <a
                  href={item.referenceUrl}
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"
                  aria-label={`${item.referenceTitle}, opens in a new tab`}
                >
                  <span class="reference-title">
                    {item.referenceTitle}
                  </span>

                  <span class="reference-source">
                    {item.referenceSource}
                  </span>

                  <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">↗</span>
                </a>
              </div>
            </article>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </section><section
  class="capability-section site-container"
  id="critical-infrastructure"
  aria-labelledby="critical-infrastructure-heading"
>
  <div class="capability-header">
    <img
      src="/images/critical-infrastructure.png"
      alt=""
      class="capability-thumbnail"
      aria-hidden="true"
    />

    <div class="capability-header-content">
      <SectionHeader
        title="Critical Infrastructure"
        id="critical-infrastructure-heading"
      />

      <p class="capability-introduction">
        Used effectively AI improves the reliability, resilience, and
        performance of critical infrastructure while improving the scalability of digital design. Examples of my work in this area include AI for energy systems, 
        industrial
        operations, and disaster response.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="example-list">
    {
      infrastructureExamples.map((item) => (
        <article class="example">
          <div class="example-description">
            <h3>{item.capability}</h3>
            <p>{item.examples}</p>
          </div>

          <div class="example-reference">
            <p class="reference-type">
              {item.referenceType}
            </p>

            <a
              href={item.referenceUrl}
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              aria-label={`${item.referenceTitle}, opens in a new tab`}
            >
              <span class="reference-title">
                {item.referenceTitle}
              </span>

              <span class="reference-source">
                {item.referenceSource}
              </span>

              <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">
                ↗
              </span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </article>
      ))
    }
  </div>
</section>

<section
  class="capability-section site-container"
  id="healthcare"
  aria-labelledby="healthcare-heading"
>
  <div class="capability-header">
    <img
      src="/images/healthcare.png"
      alt=""
      class="capability-thumbnail"
      aria-hidden="true"
    />

    <div class="capability-header-content">
      <SectionHeader
        title="Healthcare"
        id="healthcare-heading"
      />

      <p class="capability-introduction">
        AI in healthcare AI can improve patient outcomes, accelerate scientific
        discovery, and enhance the delivery of care. But it must be designed and used responsibly, protecting sensitive information and built to the highest standards. 
        I've worked on and overseen trusted 
        health AI solutions that range from biomedical research to  medical imaging to healthcare operations.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="example-list">
    {
      healthcareExamples.map((item) => (
        <article class="example">
          <div class="example-description">
            <h3>{item.capability}</h3>
            <p>{item.examples}</p>
          </div>

          <div class="example-reference">
            <p class="reference-type">
              {item.referenceType}
            </p>

            <a
              href={item.referenceUrl}
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              aria-label={`${item.referenceTitle}, opens in a new tab`}
            >
              <span class="reference-title">
                {item.referenceTitle}
              </span>

              <span class="reference-source">
                {item.referenceSource}
              </span>

              <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">
                ↗
              </span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </article>
      ))
    }
  </div>
</section>
<section
  class="capability-section site-container"
  id="decision-intelligence"
  aria-labelledby="decision-intelligence-heading"
>
  <div class="capability-header">
    <img
      src="/images/decision-intelligence.png"
      alt=""
      class="capability-thumbnail"
      aria-hidden="true"
    />

    <div class="capability-header-content">
      <SectionHeader
        title="Decision Intelligence"
        id="decision-intelligence-heading"
      />

      <p class="capability-introduction">
        Decision intelligence driven by AI transforms data into actionable insight,
        helping people make faster, better-informed decisions in complex
        environments. I've developed and governed decision intelligence solutions that span command and control, predictive analytics, and
        intelligence analysis.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="example-list">
    {
      decisionExamples.map((item) => (
        <article class="example">
          <div class="example-description">
            <h3>{item.capability}</h3>
            <p>{item.examples}</p>
          </div>

          <div class="example-reference">
            <p class="reference-type">
              {item.referenceType}
            </p>

            <a
              href={item.referenceUrl}
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              aria-label={`${item.referenceTitle}, opens in a new tab`}
            >
              <span class="reference-title">
                {item.referenceTitle}
              </span>

              <span class="reference-source">
                {item.referenceSource}
              </span>

              <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">
                ↗
              </span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </article>
      ))
    }
  </div>
</section>

  </main>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .page-introduction {
    padding:
      clamp(3.5rem, 6vw, 5.5rem) 0
      clamp(3rem, 5vw, 4.5rem);
  }

  .page-introduction h1 {
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(2.7rem, 5vw, 4.5rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: -0.035em;
  }

  .page-introduction > div > p {
    max-width: 850px;
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1.6vw, 1.2rem);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .page-introduction .scope-note {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin-top: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.96rem;
  }

  .capability-section {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 140px minmax(0, 1fr);
    column-gap: 1.5rem;
    padding-top: 1rem;
    padding-bottom: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    scroll-margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .capability-header {
    display: contents;
  }

  .capability-thumbnail {
    grid-column: 1;
    width: 140px;
    height: auto;
  }

  .capability-header-content {
    grid-column: 2;
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .capability-introduction {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0.2rem 0 0;
    color: var(--text);
    font-size: clamp(1.02rem, 1.4vw, 1.14rem);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .example-list {
    grid-column: 2;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .example {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns:
      minmax(270px, 0.85fr)
      minmax(360px, 1.4fr);
    gap: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 5rem);
    align-items: center;
    padding: 1.75rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  .example-description h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.35rem;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.3rem, 2vw, 1.65rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.25;
  }

  .example-description p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .example-reference {
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .reference-type {
    margin: 0 0 0.35rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .example-reference a {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
    grid-template-areas:
      "title arrow"
      "source arrow";
    gap: 0.15rem 1.25rem;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.15rem 0;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .reference-title {
    grid-area: title;
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .reference-source {
    grid-area: source;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.88rem;
  }

  .arrow {
    grid-area: arrow;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    transition: transform 150ms ease;
  }

  .example-reference a:hover .reference-title,
  .example-reference a:focus-visible .reference-title {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 0.2rem;
  }

  .example-reference a:hover .arrow,
  .example-reference a:focus-visible .arrow {
    transform: translate(0.15rem, -0.15rem);
  }

  .capability-header-content :global(.section-header h2) {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 800px) {
    .capability-section {
      grid-template-columns: 110px minmax(0, 1fr);
      column-gap: 1.15rem;
    }

    .capability-thumbnail {
      width: 110px;
    }

    .example {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .capability-section {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .capability-thumbnail,
    .capability-header-content,
    .example-list {
      grid-column: 1;
    }

    .capability-thumbnail {
      width: 140px;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>